d hair and a mustache appears by the ocean, holding the same round glass cup of dark coffee. He sips, looks down at the cup, then smiles with visible dimples, as if enjoying the taste. The commercial then shows a close demonstration of the product: an open Nescafé regular jar fills the view, its red-orange label reading “NESCAFÉ” and “instant coffee.” A spoon dips into the granules and lifts out a spoonful. The spoon moves over the globe-shaped glass mug, and the dark granules drop inside. A stream of hot water is poured into the mug, making the coffee swirl from golden brown to a deeper brown as steam rises. A Nescafé jar stands blurred in the background.\n\nThe image blends into a close-up of the green-labeled jar. The label is clearly readable: “NESCAFÉ decaffeinated instant coffee,” with a green cup illustration and the words “97% caffeine free.” The jar fills more and more of the screen, emphasizing the green lid and green label. This then dissolves to a light-skinned woman with short, curly brown hair wearing a patterned jacket or sweater. She holds the round glass cup with both fingers around the handle, sips the dark coffee, and then smiles gently, her eyes bright and relaxed.\n\nThe woman is then seen sitting outdoors on the rocky coast with the sandy-haired man. The ocean and dark rocks are behind them. He sits to the left in a blue jacket or shirt, holding his glass cup close and drinking. She sits to the right, facing him, holding her cup and smiling. They appear to be sharing a quiet coffee break together on the rocks; she raises her cup and drinks while he glances toward her and then down at his own cup.\n\nAt the end, the two Nescafé jars are displayed prominently on a rock in the foreground, sharply in focus. The regular Nescafé jar with the red-orange label and orange lid stands on the left, and the Nescafé decaffeinated jar with the green label and green lid stands on the right. Behind them, softly blurred, the couple remains seated by the sea with